<section class="content-section">
  <div class="section-heading">Why per-mg pricing matters</div>
  <p>A 5 mg vial for $28 sounds cheaper than a 10 mg vial for $45, but it is not. Per milligram, that "cheap" vial costs $5.60/mg vs. $4.50/mg for the larger one. Multiply that across a full research protocol and the difference is significant.</p>
  <p>Vendors know this, which is why pricing is rarely presented per mg. Peptide Price Lab removes that friction entirely, giving you the one number that actually matters for comparison: cost per milligram.</p>
</section>

